## Superseded from ci-cd-coredump-capture-container-namespace-fix

```yaml
name: ci-cd-coredump-capture-container-namespace-fix
description: "GHA workflow capturing core dumps from a process that crashes inside a Podman/Docker container must use a path that exists in BOTH host and container mount namespaces, AND must always write metadata + symbols even when no cores exist."
category: ci-cd
date: 2026-05-10
version: "1.0.0"
verification: verified-precommit
```

GHA workflow capturing core dumps from a process that crashes inside a Podman/Docker container must use a path that exists in BOTH host and container mount namespaces. Four failure modes: (1) core_pattern set to host CWD not visible inside container, (2) collect step exiting on empty cores skipping metadata, (3) if-no-files-found: ignore hiding broken capture, (4) ulimit -c applied only to a transient exec not the crashing exec. Verified on ProjectOdyssey PRs #5378/#5380.

---

## Superseded from gha-mojo-coredump-capture

```yaml
name: gha-mojo-coredump-capture
description: "Use when investigating a CI-only Mojo crash whose published trace ends in <unmapped> at frame 4."
category: ci-cd
date: 2026-05-09
version: "1.0.0"
verification: verified-ci
```

Host-side GHA infrastructure for capturing Mojo JIT crash coredumps: kernel core_pattern, systemd-coredump stop, artifact bundling. Covers two trust domains (GHA runner host root-capable vs test container unprivileged). Library filter to libKGEN*/libAsync*/libMojo*/libMSupport* keeps artifact under 1 GB GHA ceiling. Verified on ProjectOdyssey PRs #5363, #5364.

