## Superseded from debugging-mojo-jit-crash-capture-gdb-wrapper

```yaml
name: debugging-mojo-jit-crash-capture-gdb-wrapper
description: "Use when Mojo 1.0 runtime crashes but kernel core_pattern + ulimit -c unlimited produce no core because libKGENCompilerRTShared.so installs an in-process signal handler."
category: debugging
date: 2026-05-10
version: "1.0.0"
verification: verified-ci
```

Reusable wrapper scripts/mojo-under-gdb.sh: runs mojo under gdb via pixi run, uses Python gdb.events.stop filtered to SignalEvent (not hook-stop which fires on exit in gdb 15.1), writes exit code to temp file (--return-child-result unreliable in batch mode), handles SIGILL in addition to SIGABRT/SIGSEGV (Mojo os.abort() lowers to llvm.trap → SIGILL). Captured 7 real ELF cores on ProjectOdyssey CI run 25649843238 that bare ulimit approach missed entirely.
